1
00:00:16,182 --> 00:00:21,188
BLACKBOARDS
a film by Samira MAKHMALBAF

2
00:01:19,446 --> 00:01:20,652
- Said!
- Yes?

3
00:01:20,814 --> 00:01:22,725
Thanks for your water.

4
00:01:22,882 --> 00:01:25,761
- You've drunk it all!
- I was thirsty. I'm sorry.

5
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:27,429
Forget it.

6
00:01:27,487 --> 00:01:29,592
Where did you go yesterday?

7
00:01:29,989 --> 00:01:31,559
To Dezle.

8
00:01:31,825 --> 00:01:33,031
Why?

9
00:01:34,194 --> 00:01:36,003
Looking for pupils.

10
00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:37,608
But no luck,

11
00:01:37,730 --> 00:01:39,937
I couldn't find any.

12
00:01:40,967 --> 00:01:42,913
I was there for three days.

13
00:01:43,136 --> 00:01:45,116
- Cigarette?
- No, thanks.

14
00:01:45,538 --> 00:01:47,108
I don't smoke.

15
00:01:48,641 --> 00:01:50,143
You couldn't find any pupils?

16
00:01:50,210 --> 00:01:51,587
Not one.

17
00:01:53,746 --> 00:01:56,124
My father warned me

18
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:59,726
but I didn't listen to him

19
00:01:59,886 --> 00:02:01,263
and now,

20
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:05,065
I truly regret it.

21
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:07,597
- You studied for long?
- Two years.

22
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:10,436
You became a teacher in two years?

23
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:11,871
I worked hard.

24
00:02:12,065 --> 00:02:13,942
- You like it?
- Not really.

25
00:02:14,033 --> 00:02:15,034
Why?

26
00:02:15,368 --> 00:02:18,781
I looked for three days and I found nothing.

27
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:23,151
I didn't listen to my father.

28
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:29,255
- What did he tell you to do?
- To be a shepherd.

29
00:02:29,849 --> 00:02:31,123
I failed.

30
00:04:21,828 --> 00:04:22,932
He's gone.

31
00:04:23,162 --> 00:04:24,368
Get up.

32
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:31,210
Hurry UP!

33
00:04:45,151 --> 00:04:46,152
And your wife?

34
00:04:46,219 --> 00:04:48,130
When we got back from Tehran,

35
00:04:48,187 --> 00:04:51,794
we had a fight about the doctor.

36
00:04:52,525 --> 00:04:57,099
Her family insulted my family.
Mine responded in kind.

37
00:04:58,164 --> 00:05:00,269
So her father took her.

38
00:05:00,566 --> 00:05:02,011
Hurry up. We have to hide him.

39
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:04,641
It's been three months

40
00:05:04,737 --> 00:05:06,478
since she went back with her father.

41
00:05:06,539 --> 00:05:10,043
She left me with three kids,
one of them just a baby.

42
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,817
I tried to find him a wet nurse.

43
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:15,621
I went through a hundred families

44
00:05:16,015 --> 00:05:17,892
to find one.

45
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:19,861
As a result

46
00:05:20,253 --> 00:05:23,723
he's drunk the milk of many women,
even cows.

47
00:05:24,223 --> 00:05:27,397
He looks like a hundred different women.

48
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:30,498
He's got the eyes of one,
the ears of another.

49
00:05:30,563 --> 00:05:31,769
And he's sick.

50
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:34,740
Now I run from village to village

51
00:05:35,101 --> 00:05:37,240
looking for a pupil I can make into a doctor.

52
00:05:37,437 --> 00:05:40,941
That way, we'd never have to go into town.

53
00:05:41,307 --> 00:05:45,722
If there was a doctor in the next village,

54
00:05:46,245 --> 00:05:49,454
things would be easier.

55
00:05:49,949 --> 00:05:52,987
- You're going to make a doctor?
- Yes.

56
00:06:28,354 --> 00:06:30,834
- Which path are you taking?
- The one on the right.

57
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:33,328
It's dangerous.

58
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:37,766
- Which way are you going?
- This way.

59
00:06:38,030 --> 00:06:39,532
But it's very dangerous.

60
00:06:42,602 --> 00:06:44,206
Wait.

61
00:06:44,704 --> 00:06:47,708
I'll tell you again, it's a death trap.

62
00:06:48,274 --> 00:06:50,151
Yours is even worse.

63
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:54,154
No. Yours is more dangerous. Goodbye.

64
00:06:56,182 --> 00:06:59,254
- Where are you going now?
- To the village.

65
00:07:00,353 --> 00:07:03,061
- Can I come with you?
- If you like.

66
00:07:03,322 --> 00:07:05,893
If we go together,
do you think we'll find any pupils?

67
00:07:06,159 --> 00:07:08,070
- I'm not coming.
- Why?

68
00:07:08,227 --> 00:07:10,070
I want to go to the top.

69
00:07:10,129 --> 00:07:13,667
- How many pupils will you find?
- Two or three.

70
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,504
Fine. Keep them.

71
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:18,749
I'm going to climb to the very top.

72
00:07:23,709 --> 00:07:26,781
The villages bring me bad luck.

73
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:30,492
My fortune lies up there.

74
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:32,994
Go on, you take the villages.
I'm going up there.

75
00:07:33,219 --> 00:07:34,596
Take care.

76
00:07:35,588 --> 00:07:36,931
Goodbye.

77
00:08:20,766 --> 00:08:21,938
Hello!

78
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:24,072
Hello!

79
00:08:27,707 --> 00:08:30,017
Is there a school here?

80
00:08:30,109 --> 00:08:31,588
I don't know.

81
00:08:32,712 --> 00:08:34,214
And a teacher?

82
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:36,326
I don't know.

83
00:08:37,683 --> 00:08:39,094
No idea.

84
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,555
Goodbye.

85
00:08:41,621 --> 00:08:43,532
- And I'm sorry.
- The Lord go with you.

86
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:46,200
Excuse me!

87
00:08:46,726 --> 00:08:48,228
Wait a minute.

88
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:49,832
What?

89
00:08:57,637 --> 00:09:00,277
Please, read me this letter.

90
00:09:09,815 --> 00:09:11,192
What is it?

91
00:09:11,751 --> 00:09:13,389
What does he say?

92
00:09:15,988 --> 00:09:17,797
Hold on.

93
00:09:19,926 --> 00:09:21,166
Where does it come from?

94
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:24,139
This letter isn't in Persian.

95
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:27,370
For the love of God, read it to me.

96
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:32,315
It's from your son? It's not in Persian.
Maybe Arabic?

97
00:09:36,108 --> 00:09:37,610
Where's it from?

98
00:09:37,677 --> 00:09:39,782
From Iraq.

99
00:09:41,547 --> 00:09:45,962
I don't know if it's in Arabic,
Turkish or Kurdish.

100
00:09:47,053 --> 00:09:48,691
It's from my son.

101
00:09:48,988 --> 00:09:52,060
But from where? I can't read it.

102
00:09:57,296 --> 00:10:00,106
He writes that he's in good health.

103
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:02,472
He sends his regards to you.

104
00:10:03,669 --> 00:10:05,273
I return them.

105
00:10:05,738 --> 00:10:08,048
Next, he greets his mother,

106
00:10:09,241 --> 00:10:12,950
his sister, his father and his brother

107
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:17,053
and no doubt his uncles and his aunts...

108
00:10:18,017 --> 00:10:19,052
Wait.

109
00:10:20,753 --> 00:10:23,427
He finishes by saying goodbye.

110
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:26,903
But how is he getting by?
Has he got money?

111
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:30,569
I'm getting to that.

112
00:10:32,765 --> 00:10:35,803
I think he's saying that he's got a little.

113
00:10:35,868 --> 00:10:36,869
Iraqi dinars.

114
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:39,916
How's he getting on in jail?

115
00:10:41,574 --> 00:10:44,020
I'm sure he's fine...

116
00:10:48,681 --> 00:10:52,322
He must have written that he misses you.

117
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,322
At the end, he says goodbye.

118
00:10:56,389 --> 00:10:59,927
He doesn't say when he'll be released?

119
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:07,838
Goodbye.

120
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:10,204
I don't know.

121
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:13,443
But when will he be freed?

122
00:11:15,408 --> 00:11:16,853
That's all?

123
00:11:17,943 --> 00:11:21,322
If it's God's will, he will be released.
Don't worry.

124
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:27,692
Goodbye.

125
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:31,357
My God!

126
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,310
Young man!

127
00:12:50,002 --> 00:12:52,539
- Are you okay?
- Yes, thank you.

128
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:58,213
Do you know where I can find
the shepherd boys?

129
00:12:58,677 --> 00:13:01,487
Up there. This way or that way.

130
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:06,589
The goats go up this way?

131
00:13:09,188 --> 00:13:11,293
Listen, I am a teacher.

132
00:13:12,224 --> 00:13:14,636
- What?
- I am a teacher.

133
00:13:15,494 --> 00:13:17,303
So what are you doing here?

134
00:13:17,429 --> 00:13:20,035
- Looking for children.
- Good luck.

135
00:13:20,566 --> 00:13:23,069
- Where are they?
- Up there.

136
00:13:23,402 --> 00:13:25,746
Listen, young man, I'm talking to you.

137
00:13:25,838 --> 00:13:28,341
I've already told you, they're up there.

138
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,579
- Which way should I go?
- The way I told you.

139
00:13:30,843 --> 00:13:32,379
Straight ahead.

140
00:13:35,915 --> 00:13:38,259
Do you know how to write?

141
00:13:39,685 --> 00:13:41,255
Do you know how to write?

142
00:13:41,787 --> 00:13:42,822
What?

143
00:13:43,055 --> 00:13:44,090
To read and write?

144
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:45,226
No.

145
00:13:46,058 --> 00:13:48,095
Would you like to learn?

146
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:49,833
It's useless.

147
00:13:49,895 --> 00:13:50,965
I'm talking to you!

148
00:13:51,897 --> 00:13:53,308
Show me the way.

149
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:56,808
The way, young man!

150
00:13:57,803 --> 00:13:59,714
Where are you going?

151
00:13:59,805 --> 00:14:01,409
- Young man!
- What?

152
00:14:01,473 --> 00:14:02,508
The way?

153
00:14:02,575 --> 00:14:05,249
Here. There. Also here.

154
00:14:06,579 --> 00:14:08,081
Not this way?

155
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,050
I'm talking to you!

156
00:14:10,115 --> 00:14:11,685
- Young man!
- What?

157
00:14:12,785 --> 00:14:14,389
Show me the way.

158
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:17,390
I want you to show me the way. Look at me!

159
00:14:18,057 --> 00:14:19,593
Leave me alone.

160
00:14:22,061 --> 00:14:23,540
Anybody here?

161
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:26,176
Anybody here?

162
00:14:26,632 --> 00:14:28,441
Is there anyone here?

163
00:14:31,470 --> 00:14:34,974
Open the windows. Answer me!

164
00:14:41,914 --> 00:14:44,326
Multiplication tables!

165
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:49,097
Come and learn how to multiply.

166
00:14:51,156 --> 00:14:52,965
One times two is two.

167
00:14:53,926 --> 00:14:56,566
Two times two is four.

168
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,708
Madam!

169
00:15:02,635 --> 00:15:04,546
Do you need a teacher?

170
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:07,350
- What?
- I am a teacher.

171
00:15:07,673 --> 00:15:09,619
Where are your children?

172
00:15:09,675 --> 00:15:11,450
Leave me alone.

173
00:15:15,514 --> 00:15:17,653
I have come to teach your children.

174
00:15:17,816 --> 00:15:20,023
- Who are you?
- I am a teacher.

175
00:15:20,219 --> 00:15:23,223
- Good for you.
- I'm looking for pupils.

176
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:29,262
- Where are the children?
- Go away.

177
00:15:52,351 --> 00:15:53,830
Anybody here?

178
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:56,399
Anybody here?

179
00:15:57,222 --> 00:15:59,065
Is there anyone here?

180
00:16:00,092 --> 00:16:02,971
I can hear voices.

181
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:06,500
I've come a long way

182
00:16:06,598 --> 00:16:08,703
to teach your children

183
00:16:08,767 --> 00:16:11,008
to read and write.

184
00:16:12,104 --> 00:16:14,778
You won't need to pay me much.

185
00:16:16,709 --> 00:16:19,451
I'll teach you to read and write letters.

186
00:16:42,768 --> 00:16:45,647
Children, at last! Wonderful! Come here.

187
00:16:47,373 --> 00:16:50,946
Stop. Tell me where you've come from.

188
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,847
Where are you going?

189
00:16:56,115 --> 00:16:57,958
Where have you come from?

190
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,190
Where have you come from?

191
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:04,527
I've come from deep in the valley
to find you.

192
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:06,935
Let us through, mister.

193
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:10,096
Just a moment.

194
00:17:10,262 --> 00:17:12,139
I'm not going to eat you.

195
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:14,605
I only want to talk to you.

196
00:17:16,568 --> 00:17:19,139
- Do you have a school here?
- No.

197
00:17:20,205 --> 00:17:22,082
- And a teacher?
- No.

198
00:17:23,142 --> 00:17:24,883
- Would you like one?
- No.

199
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:27,822
Where are you going with those burdens?

200
00:17:28,180 --> 00:17:30,285
- We're mules.
- What?

201
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:33,193
- Then I'll come with you, okay?
- No.

202
00:17:33,585 --> 00:17:35,565
Let us get past, mister.

203
00:17:36,088 --> 00:17:37,692
Let us get past!

204
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:40,161
Wait a minute, kid!

205
00:17:40,793 --> 00:17:43,740
Allow me to finish and I'll let you go.

206
00:17:44,797 --> 00:17:48,006
Just one question:
where are you going with those?

207
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,238
Let us get past!

208
00:17:51,036 --> 00:17:53,380
It's heavy! You can't stay there like that.

209
00:17:54,039 --> 00:17:55,313
Let us get past.

210
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:56,943
We're wiped out.

211
00:17:57,009 --> 00:17:59,148
- You don't have a teacher?
- No.

212
00:17:59,812 --> 00:18:01,257
There's no teachers here.

213
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,859
- Where are you going?
- I don't know.

214
00:18:03,982 --> 00:18:05,359
You don't know?

215
00:18:06,051 --> 00:18:08,258
Let us pass, we're wiped out.

216
00:18:08,887 --> 00:18:09,991
Look.

217
00:18:11,023 --> 00:18:13,025
You're holding us all up.

218
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:15,761
Let us pass.

219
00:18:49,228 --> 00:18:50,707
I'm a teacher

220
00:18:51,163 --> 00:18:53,609
and I've come
to teach you to read and write.

221
00:18:53,866 --> 00:18:56,403
I've come a long way.

222
00:18:57,369 --> 00:19:00,179
I've been looking for you for a long time!

223
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:06,453
I want to teach you to read and write,

224
00:19:06,912 --> 00:19:09,950
to add up and multiply.

225
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:13,862
I don't want a lot of money.

226
00:19:14,052 --> 00:19:15,998
If you don't have any,

227
00:19:16,121 --> 00:19:19,034
you could just give me something to eat.

228
00:19:19,925 --> 00:19:22,735
We carry contraband, stolen goods.

229
00:19:23,395 --> 00:19:25,136
We take it

230
00:19:27,199 --> 00:19:28,974
over the border

231
00:19:29,501 --> 00:19:31,742
between Iran and Iraq.

232
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:35,574
We're always on the run.

233
00:19:38,443 --> 00:19:39,717
Listen, my child.

234
00:19:39,778 --> 00:19:41,416
With education,

235
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:44,828
you will be able to read a book

236
00:19:45,284 --> 00:19:48,026
or, even better, a newspaper

237
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:51,000
when you're traveling.

238
00:19:51,123 --> 00:19:53,069
Learn to read and write!

239
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:56,106
You'll know what's going on in the world.

240
00:19:57,429 --> 00:20:00,433
You can learn to add up,

241
00:20:01,166 --> 00:20:04,704
to subtract, to do your accounts
without being swindled.

242
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:07,107
What good is it, all that?

243
00:20:07,172 --> 00:20:11,587
You can study or find work.

244
00:20:14,513 --> 00:20:17,653
Doing the accounts,

245
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:19,793
that's great for the Boss.

246
00:20:19,851 --> 00:20:21,455
Us, we're mules.

247
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:24,056
Always on the move.

248
00:20:24,790 --> 00:20:27,031
How do you expect us to read?

249
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:29,201
To read a book,

250
00:20:30,963 --> 00:20:33,136
you have to sit down.

251
00:20:33,198 --> 00:20:35,644
Us, we never stop moving.

252
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:53,518
Listen, I want to talk to you.

253
00:20:58,724 --> 00:21:00,203
Stop! Wait!

254
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:01,863
Wait!

255
00:21:09,468 --> 00:21:11,209
Hello!

256
00:21:12,004 --> 00:21:14,450
Do you know how to read and write?

257
00:21:14,673 --> 00:21:16,846
- Do you?
- No.

258
00:21:17,309 --> 00:21:19,516
- Do you want to learn?
- No.

259
00:21:19,845 --> 00:21:21,483
- You don't?
- No.

260
00:21:23,215 --> 00:21:24,421
Hello.

261
00:21:26,084 --> 00:21:28,530
Do you know how to read and write?

262
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:31,059
- Do you?
- No.

263
00:21:37,262 --> 00:21:38,639
Hello, sir!

264
00:21:39,564 --> 00:21:41,544
- I'm talking to you.
- What?

265
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,739
You wouldn't have a scrap of bread?

266
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:45,748
It's freezing!

267
00:21:46,371 --> 00:21:48,282
Where are you going?

268
00:21:49,341 --> 00:21:51,947
I don't have a job, can I come with you?

269
00:21:52,010 --> 00:21:53,683
We don't need you.

270
00:22:02,888 --> 00:22:05,027
Hello. How's it going?

271
00:22:06,391 --> 00:22:07,961
It's freezing!

272
00:22:10,796 --> 00:22:12,173
Hello, sir.

273
00:22:12,864 --> 00:22:14,104
Sir!

274
00:22:16,868 --> 00:22:18,142
I'm talking to you.

275
00:22:21,573 --> 00:22:23,780
Why won't you answer me?

