00:50:09,473 --> 00:50:11,384
Most of them, yes.

552
00:50:12,309 --> 00:50:15,813
But their mothers told them
never to trust strangers.

553
00:50:22,085 --> 00:50:24,429
Children. Listen to me a minute.

554
00:50:24,588 --> 00:50:25,862
Sit down.

555
00:50:26,056 --> 00:50:28,127
Don't waste what time you have.

556
00:50:28,191 --> 00:50:30,228
Let me teach you.

557
00:50:31,395 --> 00:50:35,343
Look at my blackboard!

558
00:50:38,268 --> 00:50:41,545
I want to teach you to read and write.

559
00:50:42,339 --> 00:50:45,513
Watch me! Listen to me!

560
00:50:45,942 --> 00:50:47,717
Don't listen to him.

561
00:50:49,846 --> 00:50:52,452
Let's get out of here!

562
00:50:52,949 --> 00:50:55,930
Children! Where are you going?

563
00:51:01,491 --> 00:51:02,492
Let's go! Carry him.

564
00:51:04,127 --> 00:51:05,333
Stop!

565
00:51:06,763 --> 00:51:08,367
Listen to me!

566
00:51:09,166 --> 00:51:10,167
Don't go!

567
00:51:10,233 --> 00:51:11,610
It's your fault, all this!

568
00:51:11,968 --> 00:51:13,276
Children!

569
00:51:39,996 --> 00:51:41,976
- Repeat.
- Did I say it right?

570
00:51:42,165 --> 00:51:43,473
Well done.

571
00:51:48,371 --> 00:51:49,406
Very good.

572
00:51:51,408 --> 00:51:52,648
Stretch out the R...

573
00:51:56,480 --> 00:51:59,586
R like Reeboir.

574
00:52:00,283 --> 00:52:02,524
Listen, friend.

575
00:52:02,786 --> 00:52:04,732
The other story wasn't true.

576
00:52:04,788 --> 00:52:07,667
What happened: we chased the rabbit,

577
00:52:07,824 --> 00:52:09,235
we caught it

578
00:52:09,493 --> 00:52:11,404
and we ate it.

579
00:52:12,062 --> 00:52:14,440
It was tasty!

580
00:52:14,898 --> 00:52:17,242
Delicious!

581
00:53:31,741 --> 00:53:34,745
A like Apple...

582
00:53:36,146 --> 00:53:38,592
Be quiet. They're behind us.

583
00:53:40,317 --> 00:53:42,661
Reeboir and his group, this way.

584
00:53:43,587 --> 00:53:45,965
Group Two, take the other path.

585
00:53:48,959 --> 00:53:51,667
The rest of you, follow me.

586
00:53:51,995 --> 00:53:53,975
Be careful. It's dangerous.

587
00:54:08,378 --> 00:54:12,326
Not this way!
There are land mines everywhere!

588
00:54:13,683 --> 00:54:15,629
Take the other path.

589
00:54:16,019 --> 00:54:18,021
Look out!

590
00:54:18,355 --> 00:54:22,531
Don't get yourselves killed.

591
00:54:27,297 --> 00:54:29,709
Go round the other side!

592
00:55:05,869 --> 00:55:07,109
Two times two?

593
00:55:08,505 --> 00:55:09,609
Four.

594
00:55:10,540 --> 00:55:11,712
Reply!

595
00:55:12,842 --> 00:55:15,049
Reply swiftly, learn swiftly.

596
00:55:15,612 --> 00:55:17,216
Two times three?

597
00:55:18,315 --> 00:55:19,385
Six.

598
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:23,521
Four times two?

599
00:55:23,653 --> 00:55:25,132
Come on, answer!

600
00:55:30,994 --> 00:55:32,530
Two times five?

601
00:55:34,364 --> 00:55:35,968
Come on: ten!

602
00:55:37,033 --> 00:55:39,775
To learn quickly, you must answer quickly.

603
00:55:43,206 --> 00:55:44,708
One times two?

604
00:55:45,642 --> 00:55:46,712
Two.

605
00:55:47,877 --> 00:55:50,153
Two times two? Four.

606
00:55:52,182 --> 00:55:53,923
One times two? Two.

607
00:56:01,391 --> 00:56:03,132
Mother, a rabbit!

608
00:56:23,380 --> 00:56:24,552
Chuan!

609
00:56:25,448 --> 00:56:28,190
What are you doing? The Devil take you!

610
00:56:30,620 --> 00:56:31,860
Halaleh!

611
00:56:34,924 --> 00:56:36,835
Where is she gone?

612
00:56:52,942 --> 00:56:54,751
The Devil take you!

613
00:57:01,618 --> 00:57:02,858
Halaleh!

614
00:57:03,453 --> 00:57:04,955
Where are you?

615
00:57:17,200 --> 00:57:19,703
Please, sir, have you seen my wife?

616
00:57:39,856 --> 00:57:41,631
Where are you going?

617
00:57:42,325 --> 00:57:43,702
Stop...

618
00:57:55,939 --> 00:57:58,180
You want some walnuts?

619
00:58:04,280 --> 00:58:06,089
One times two is two!

620
00:58:12,021 --> 00:58:14,566
Why are you running away?

621
00:58:14,591 --> 00:58:14,728
Why are you running away?

622
00:58:16,626 --> 00:58:18,765
Have I done something wrong?

623
00:58:20,763 --> 00:58:22,606
If math is too difficult,

624
00:58:22,665 --> 00:58:24,576
I'll teach you to read.

625
00:58:24,734 --> 00:58:26,680
Repeat after me...

626
00:58:29,372 --> 00:58:32,182
"I love you."

627
00:58:33,977 --> 00:58:35,513
See, it's easy.

628
00:58:37,080 --> 00:58:38,457
Say it!

629
00:58:39,415 --> 00:58:41,258
Come on, say it!

630
00:58:42,418 --> 00:58:44,295
Say, "I love you."

631
00:58:46,322 --> 00:58:47,699
Look at me.

632
00:58:54,564 --> 00:58:56,475
What sort of student are you?

633
00:58:56,566 --> 00:58:58,341
I'll give you eight.

634
00:59:01,638 --> 00:59:02,878
No, not eight.

635
00:59:03,072 --> 00:59:05,177
That would fail you.

636
00:59:06,209 --> 00:59:07,882
I'll give you ten,

637
00:59:08,478 --> 00:59:09,889
so you pass.

638
00:59:14,717 --> 00:59:15,923
Say it!

639
00:59:17,320 --> 00:59:18,958
Say, "I love you."

640
00:59:19,622 --> 00:59:21,295
You don't want to?

641
00:59:22,158 --> 00:59:24,365
What sort of student are you?

642
00:59:25,461 --> 00:59:27,566
I'm giving you zero.

643
00:59:31,901 --> 00:59:34,438
At least say that you don't love me.

644
00:59:37,874 --> 00:59:39,353
What's wrong?

645
00:59:40,410 --> 00:59:42,447
You won't say that either?

646
00:59:45,715 --> 00:59:47,786
Here comes another zero.

647
00:59:48,151 --> 00:59:49,494
Happy now?

648
00:59:51,087 --> 00:59:53,363
Now a zero for your son.

649
00:59:55,058 --> 00:59:57,163
Here's a zero for your son.

650
00:59:58,861 --> 00:59:59,965
What?

651
01:00:01,331 --> 01:00:05,336
You still won't answer?
I'll give you a zero for your father.

652
01:00:07,570 --> 01:00:08,674
Here.

653
01:00:16,546 --> 01:00:18,617
Still got nothing to say?

654
01:00:19,449 --> 01:00:21,087
I'll give myself a zero.

655
01:00:21,150 --> 01:00:24,529
For having been stupid enough
to follow you.

656
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:27,764
What kind of a life is this?

657
01:00:27,824 --> 01:00:28,894
Goodbye.

658
01:00:36,633 --> 01:00:38,442
How could I have loved you?

659
01:00:38,635 --> 01:00:40,945
You're not listening to me!

660
01:00:45,174 --> 01:00:46,551
Blackboard!

661
01:00:48,277 --> 01:00:49,551
Stop!

662
01:00:50,213 --> 01:00:51,590
Blackboard!

663
01:00:55,284 --> 01:00:56,388
Stop.

664
01:01:08,665 --> 01:01:10,338
Listen!

665
01:01:25,448 --> 01:01:27,951
My heart is like a train.

666
01:01:28,017 --> 01:01:31,294
At every station, someone gets on or off.

667
01:01:31,354 --> 01:01:35,530
But there is someone who never gets off.

668
01:01:38,027 --> 01:01:39,802
My son.

669
01:01:45,068 --> 01:01:46,411
Halaleh...

670
01:01:46,803 --> 01:01:48,749
What's happening?

671
01:02:07,690 --> 01:02:10,296
Escape! Hurry up!

672
01:02:10,626 --> 01:02:13,232
What's going on?

673
01:02:21,671 --> 01:02:26,347
The soldiers at the border have opened fire!

674
01:03:57,533 --> 01:03:59,706
A like Apple.

675
01:04:00,803 --> 01:04:03,374
Break the syllables up.

676
01:04:25,094 --> 01:04:28,075
Excuse me, sir. I'm sorry.

677
01:04:29,065 --> 01:04:32,376
We're in danger. I'll come back later.

678
01:06:22,311 --> 01:06:23,585
Halt!

679
01:06:24,613 --> 01:06:26,820
Who goes there?

680
01:06:59,315 --> 01:07:00,953
What's your name?

681
01:07:02,084 --> 01:07:05,224
- You don't want to tell me?
- Ghazal.

682
01:07:06,489 --> 01:07:09,265
Do you know how to read and write?

683
01:07:11,127 --> 01:07:12,629
- Do you?
- No.

684
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:17,238
- Where is your village?
- Down there.

685
01:07:17,466 --> 01:07:19,139
- That's Dezle?
- Yes.

686
01:07:20,102 --> 01:07:22,582
- Is there a school?
- No.

687
01:07:23,873 --> 01:07:26,149
- Do you want a teacher?
- No.

688
01:07:56,939 --> 01:07:59,920
- Will we have to wait long?
- Who knows.

689
01:07:59,975 --> 01:08:01,579
Where are your friends?

690
01:08:01,644 --> 01:08:03,885
We're meeting up by the river.

691
01:08:04,080 --> 01:08:06,856
No, it was near the goats.

692
01:08:07,116 --> 01:08:09,619
- They're not coming.
- They've been caught.

693
01:08:18,994 --> 01:08:22,271
Thanks for the milk. Excellent.

694
01:08:50,960 --> 01:08:53,634
Sir, I've written something.

695
01:08:56,599 --> 01:08:58,476
- I wrote something.
- What?

696
01:08:58,534 --> 01:09:01,037
- I wrote my name.
- Well done.

697
01:09:01,203 --> 01:09:03,183
I wrote "Reeboir."

698
01:09:04,673 --> 01:09:07,313
Run for your life!

699
01:09:35,070 --> 01:09:36,515
Take him.

700
01:09:36,605 --> 01:09:37,845
Come.

701
01:09:38,073 --> 01:09:39,416
Quick.

702
01:09:41,177 --> 01:09:43,487
It's just like at Halebtcheh...

703
01:09:50,452 --> 01:09:53,399
I built a wall to protect us

704
01:09:54,056 --> 01:09:56,730
from chemical weapons.

705
01:10:01,830 --> 01:10:03,503
Father!

706
01:10:14,376 --> 01:10:16,549
Chemical weapons...

707
01:10:17,513 --> 01:10:18,719
Father!

708
01:10:34,129 --> 01:10:35,665
Look after him.

709
01:10:50,646 --> 01:10:52,387
Chemical weapons...

710
01:10:52,481 --> 01:10:54,552
What's happened?

711
01:10:55,084 --> 01:10:56,791
I pissed.

712
01:11:00,489 --> 01:11:03,060
Hide under the blackboard.

713
01:11:08,063 --> 01:11:09,838
My daughter!

714
01:11:20,542 --> 01:11:23,113
Your brother is dead. Let's go.

715
01:11:24,113 --> 01:11:27,287
He isn't dead.
He wanted to die in his homeland.

716
01:11:27,583 --> 01:11:29,995
Come on. He is dead.

717
01:11:58,614 --> 01:12:01,322
Just like at Halebtcheh.

718
01:12:09,458 --> 01:12:12,371
It's not chemical weapons. It's rifle fire.

719
01:12:13,395 --> 01:12:15,033
Don't worry.

720
01:12:16,832 --> 01:12:19,574
It's the soldiers from over the border

721
01:12:19,968 --> 01:12:21,879
who were firing.

722
01:12:25,641 --> 01:12:27,951
It's not chemical weapons.

723
01:12:28,210 --> 01:12:29,553
Don't be afraid, my darling.

724
01:12:29,611 --> 01:12:31,090
The women...

725
01:12:31,180 --> 01:12:32,750
The children...

726
01:12:40,422 --> 01:12:42,868
We're not going to die.

727
01:12:44,193 --> 01:12:46,264
It's not chemical weapons.

728
01:12:46,695 --> 01:12:49,141
It's the soldiers, over the border.

729
01:12:49,765 --> 01:12:52,371
If they hear us, they'll fire.

730
01:12:52,468 --> 01:12:55,972
I swear, it's not chemical weapons.

731
01:12:58,941 --> 01:13:00,352
The women...

732
01:13:00,909 --> 01:13:02,252
The men...

733
01:13:28,904 --> 01:13:31,748
Hide under the blackboard.

734
01:13:32,007 --> 01:13:34,044
I'll protect you.

735
01:14:24,259 --> 01:14:25,863
Stop!

736
01:14:31,300 --> 01:14:33,644
There. The border.

737
01:14:33,936 --> 01:14:35,847
The land of your fathers,

738
01:14:35,904 --> 01:14:37,577
of your ancestors.

739
01:14:38,040 --> 01:14:39,883
Your homeland!

740
01:14:39,975 --> 01:14:42,046
You're lying!

741
01:14:42,611 --> 01:14:44,249
I swear I'm not.

742
01:14:44,713 --> 01:14:46,715
It's the truth. Take a good look.

743
01:14:48,784 --> 01:14:51,094
Don't you recognize Halebtcheh?

744
01:14:51,353 --> 01:14:53,629
No. It's not the border.

745
01:14:54,223 --> 01:14:56,328
He's tricked us, I know it.

746
01:14:56,492 --> 01:15:00,372
He's lying. It's not the border.

747
01:15:03,565 --> 01:15:05,169
We are lost.

748
01:15:05,801 --> 01:15:08,281
I know our border very well. This isn't it.

749
01:15:08,470 --> 01:15:10,177
I'm not lying.

750
01:15:10,906 --> 01:15:13,147
I swear to you this is it.

751
01:15:13,208 --> 01:15:15,552
This is your homeland.

752
01:15:16,245 --> 01:15:19,886
This isn't the border! We are lost!

753
01:15:20,182 --> 01:15:22,492
Can't you understand?

754
01:15:29,758 --> 01:15:32,637
- Don't you believe me?
- You're lying.

755
01:15:32,761 --> 01:15:35,002
You've tricked us, Blackboard!

756
01:15:35,163 --> 01:15:36,733
I swear to you, I'm not lying.

757
01:15:36,798 --> 01:15:39,472
It's been like this since the bombing.

758
01:15:40,435 --> 01:15:42,142
It's not true!

759
01:15:45,374 --> 01:15:48,048
I swear to you, this is the border.

760
01:15:51,613 --> 01:15:54,093
You're looking at Halebtcheh.

761
01:15:55,217 --> 01:15:58,790
It's because of the bombing...

762
01:17:22,771 --> 01:17:24,512
God be praised!

763
01:17:24,640 --> 01:17:27,120
We are grateful to you. Here are the nuts.

764
01:17:27,242 --> 01:17:29,051
What will you do now?

765
01:17:29,544 --> 01:17:31,888
Will you cross the border with us?

766
01:17:31,947 --> 01:17:33,449
No, I can't.

767
01:17:33,982 --> 01:17:37,794
But your wife wants to cross over.
She won't stay with you.

768
01:17:37,853 --> 01:17:39,662
What's your decision?

769
01:17:39,755 --> 01:17:42,736
If she doesn't want me, what can I do?

770
01:17:43,659 --> 01:17:45,900
I don't know. You must decide.

771
01:17:46,128 --> 01:17:47,334
A divorce?

772
01:17:47,396 --> 01:17:49,706
Yes, if that's what she wants.

773
01:17:49,998 --> 01:17:51,705
Let's find out.

774
01:17:53,201 --> 01:17:56,478
Are you coming with us, Blackboard?

775
01:17:56,872 --> 01:17:59,216
I can't. I belong here, in this land.

776
01:18:00,175 --> 01:18:03,645
Your wife wants to return to her
own country. She doesn't want you.

777
01:18:03,745 --> 01:18:05,622
Did she tell you that?

778
01:18:08,850 --> 01:18:11,729
There's nothing I can do. I'll divorce her.

779
01:18:12,220 --> 01:18:14,359
- You will divorce her?
- Yes.

780
01:18:15,223 --> 01:18:16,964
Go and find her.

781
01:18:25,100 --> 01:18:26,909
Put it down here.

782
01:18:30,172 --> 01:18:31,651
Do you agree to a divorce?

783
01:18:31,707 --> 01:18:33,709
And that you will take the blackboard?

784
01:18:38,113 --> 01:18:39,990
The blackboard? Yes.

785
01:18:41,049 --> 01:18:43,325
You may look at each other

786
01:18:43,385 --> 01:18:44,887
one last time.

787
01:18:45,153 --> 01:18:46,689
Lift your hand.

788
01:18:47,989 --> 01:18:49,935
Take that stick.

789
01:18:50,926 --> 01:18:52,337
Halaleh,

790
01:18:55,297 --> 01:18:57,675
you are now divorced,

791
01:18:57,733 --> 01:18:59,906
and the blackboard is yours.

792
01:19:01,403 --> 01:19:03,713
May God keep you from hunger!

793
01:19:03,772 --> 01:19:06,309
May God keep you from thirst!

794
01:19:06,475 --> 01:19:08,785
May God keep you from solitude!

795
01:19:12,614 --> 01:19:14,423
Take your blackboard.

796
01:19:17,018 --> 01:19:18,463
And give me my stick.

797
01:19:18,987 --> 01:19:20,330
Goodbye.

798
01:19:29,297 --> 01:19:30,674
I love you

799
01:19:37,239 --> 01:19:39,719
Chuan! What are you doing?

800
01:19:40,008 --> 01:19:41,681
Hurry up. Come on.

801
01:19:42,911 --> 01:19:44,413
Come, quickly.

